 :tx/rationale "AUDIT F-C8-001 (CRITICAL): Schema Layers 1-4 hardcode DDIS ontology — the foundational C8 violation. PROBLEM: ~180 attributes across Layers 1-4 hardcode DDIS ontology in schema.rs:200-800: Layer 1 (:intent/*, :spec/*, :impl/* — trilateral model), Layer 2 (:element/*, :inv/*, :adr/*, :neg/* — spec element types), Layer 3 (:exploration/*, :promotion/*, :signal/* — discovery), Layer 4 (:topology/*, :hypothesis/*, :witness/*, :policy/* — coordination). The C8 test: 'Would this make sense for a React project?' Answer: No. React has no :spec/element-type, no :inv/* attributes, no trilateral ISP model. PolicyConfig system (policy.rs) was designed to address this but only configures weights/boundaries, not the schema itself. JUSTIFICATION: C8 is the hardest constraint. Schema determines what the system can think about — hardcoded schema means hardcoded ontology. The DDIS methodology (INV/ADR/NEG) is the first APPLICATION on the braid substrate (per CLAUDE.md purpose section), not the substrate itself. Schema::from_datoms() already exists as the C3-compliant loading mechanism. The fix requires making braid init the point where domain-specific schema enters, not the compilation step. SOLUTION: (1) Keep Layer 0 (19 meta-schema attrs) hardcoded. (2) Move Layers 1-4 to .edn policy manifest files. (3) braid init --manifest ddis.edn installs DDIS schema. (4) braid init with no manifest produces bare Layer 0 store. VERIFICATION: braid init with no manifest -> only Layer 0 attributes. braid init --manifest ddis.edn -> full DDIS schema. DEPENDENCIES: This is the foundational C8 fix. ENABLES: F-C8-002 (MaterializedViews), F-C8-003 (trilateral), F-C8-005 (innate concepts). All Wave 2 tasks depend on this. Overlaps with F-INV-004 (same finding, different dimension). FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/schema.rs:200-800, crates/braid/src/commands/init.rs. SEVERITY: Critical. WAVE: 2. EFFORT: 16h."
